codex
Root cause: the split threshold uses the wrong minimum block size.

`Block::m_previous` write sites in [MemoryManager.cpp](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/librar
y/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:395):

- [318](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.
cpp:318): prefix sentinel `setPrevious(NULL)`, only legitimate null.
- [322](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.
cpp:322): first free block previous = prefix.
- [327](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.
cpp:327): suffix sentinel previous = first free.
- [1254](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager
.cpp:1254): allocation split creates trailing free block previous = allocated block.
- [1258](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager
.cpp:1258): allocation split makes old next previous = trailing free block.
- [1562](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager
.cpp:1562): free merge-with-previous relinks next previous = previous.
- [1576](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager
.cpp:1576): free merge-with-next relinks next-after-next previous = merged block.

`addToFreeList` / `removeFromFreeList` do not intentionally write `Block::m_previous`; they write 
`FreeBlock` tree fields. The bad x64 path is:

1. `MemoryManager::allocate` removes a free block at [1245](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/l
ibrary/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1245).
2. It decides whether to split using `cms_allocatedBlockSize` at [1251](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/eng
ine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1251).
3. On x64, `cms_allocatedBlockSize == 32`, but `cms_freeBlockSize == 64` from [210-211](D:/Code/swg-c
lient-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:210). So [1251](D
:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1251)
 permits a 48-byte trailing free block.
4. `addToFreeList(block)` at [1261](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManag
er/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1261) treats that 48-byte remainder as a `FreeBlock`.
5. Exact corrupting write: [994](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/
src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:994), `freeBlock->m_parentFreeBlock = parent;`. On a 48-byte x64 free 
block, this field is at offset 48, exactly the next block’s `m_previous`. If `parent == NULL`, the 
next live allocated block gets `m_previous == NULL`.

Then `operator delete` routes through [OsNewDel.cpp:60-63](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/li
brary/sharedMemoryManager/src/win32/OsNewDel.cpp:60) or sized delete [73-76](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/sr
c/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/win32/OsNewDel.cpp:73) into `MemoryManager::free`, 
which computes the block at [1453](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManage
r/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1453) and crashes at [1557](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/li
brary/sharedMemoryManager/src/shared/MemoryManager.cpp:1557) on `block->getPrevious()->isFree()`.

Minimal fix: change [1251](D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedMemoryManager/src/sh
ared/MemoryManager.cpp:1251) to require `cms_freeBlockSize`, not `cms_allocatedBlockSize`, for the 
trailing free block:

```cpp
if (bestFreeBlock->getSize() > (allocSize + cms_freeBlockSize))
```

or preserve the old “at least one payload byte” intent:

```cpp
if (bestFreeBlock->getSize() > (allocSize + cms_freeBlockSize + 1))
```

The first is sufficient because sizes are 16-byte aligned.
